SIMPLE: phaeton
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phaëton
<hw>Pha"⟦eum⟧*ton</hw> <pr>(f⟦amac⟧"⟦esl⟧*t⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>pha⟦eacute⟧ton</ets> a kind of carriage, fr.
<ets>Pha⟦eacute⟧thon</ets> Pha⟦eum⟧thon, the son of Helios. See
<er>Pha⟦eum⟧thon</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A four-wheeled carriage
(with or without a top), open, or having no side pieces, in front of the
seat. It is drawn by one or two horses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>See <er>Pha⟦eum⟧thon</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A handsome American butterfly
(<spn>Euphydryas Pha⟦eum⟧ton</spn> syn. <spn>Melit⟦ae⟧a
Pha⟦eum⟧ton</spn>). The upper side of the wings is black, with
orange-red spots and marginal crescents, and several rows of
cream-colored spots; -- called also
<altname>Baltimore</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phagedena</ent>⟦br⟧
